    <!-- SCIENCE SECTION -->
    <h2 id="science">The Science Behind Mushrooms for Energy</h2>

    <p>Functional mushrooms enhance energy through fundamentally different mechanisms than stimulants. Understanding these pathways helps explain why mushroom-based energy is slower to onset but more sustainable than caffeine.</p>

    <div class="vs-strip">
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>ATP Production</strong>
        <p>Cordycepin upregulates adenylate cyclase, directly increasing ATP synthesis in mitochondria. More ATP = more available energy for every cell.<br /><em>Journal of Alternative and Complementary Medicine, 2010</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Oxygen Utilization</strong>
        <p>Cordyceps improves VO2 max by enhancing hemoglobin oxygen-carrying capacity and blood flow to working muscles.<br /><em>Chinese Journal of Integrative Medicine, 2014</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>NGF Stimulation</strong>
        <p>Lion's mane hericenones and erinacines stimulate nerve growth factor production, supporting cognitive energy and mental stamina.<br /><em>International Journal of Medicinal Mushrooms, 2013</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Stress Adaptation</strong>
        <p>Reishi and ashwagandha prevent cortisol-driven energy depletion, maintaining steady energy output during chronic stress periods.<br /><em>Indian Journal of Psychological Medicine, 2012</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>

