    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Mushroom Gummies for Energy</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How do mushroom gummies increase energy?</summary>
      <p>Cordyceps mushrooms increase energy through three mechanisms: enhancing mitochondrial ATP production by upregulating adenylate cyclase activity, improving oxygen utilization (VO2 max) by increasing blood flow to working muscles, and boosting cellular energy currency by increasing the ATP-to-ADP ratio. A 2010 study in the <em>Journal of Alternative and Complementary Medicine</em> found that cordyceps supplementation improved exercise tolerance by 7% in healthy adults after 12 weeks. Unlike caffeine, cordyceps generates energy at the cellular level without jitters, crashes, or sleep disruption.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Is cordyceps or lion's mane better for energy?</summary>
      <p>Cordyceps is the stronger choice for physical energy, endurance, and athletic performance due to its direct effect on mitochondrial ATP production and oxygen utilization. Lion's mane is better for mental energy, focus, and cognitive performance due to its stimulation of NGF (nerve growth factor). For comprehensive energy — both physical stamina and mental clarity — a cordyceps + lion's mane combination addresses both pathways simultaneously.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long do mushroom gummies take to boost energy?</summary>
      <p>Most users report noticeable energy improvements within 1 to 2 weeks of daily cordyceps supplementation. The ATP production and oxygen utilization benefits documented in clinical trials were measured at the 4 to 12 week mark, with peak effects at 8 weeks. Lion's mane cognitive energy effects typically become apparent within 2 to 4 weeks. For maximum results, maintain consistent daily use for at least 8 to 12 weeks before evaluating efficacy.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can mushroom gummies replace caffeine?</summary>
      <p>Mushroom gummies can partially replace caffeine for sustained, non-stimulant energy, but they operate through a fundamentally different mechanism. Caffeine blocks adenosine receptors for immediate alertness; cordyceps increases actual ATP production at the cellular level. The energy from mushrooms is slower in onset (days to weeks vs. minutes) but more sustained and without crashes. Many users successfully reduce their caffeine intake by 50 to 75% after establishing a mushroom supplement routine.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What dosage of cordyceps is effective for energy?</summary>
      <p>Clinical studies have demonstrated energy and performance benefits at doses between 1,000mg and 3,000mg per day of cordyceps extract. Most gummies deliver 500mg to 1,000mg per serving — you may need 2 servings daily to reach the upper clinical range. Products using Cordyceps militaris are preferred over sinensis due to up to 90x higher cordycepin content and sustainable cultivation.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are mushroom gummies safe to take with pre-workout supplements?</summary>
      <p>Yes, mushroom gummies are generally safe to combine with pre-workout supplements. Cordyceps and lion's mane do not contain stimulants and work through different energy pathways than caffeine, beta-alanine, or creatine. The ATP-boosting mechanism of cordyceps may actually enhance creatine's effectiveness. If your pre-workout contains very high caffeine doses (300mg+), monitor your overall response carefully.</p>
    </details>

